President Obama announced his intent to nominate Alan Cohen as a Member of the Social Security Advisory Board. Cohen previously served as the Senior Budget Advisor and Chief Counselor for Social Security for the U.S. Senate Committee on Finance. He has also held various positions related to budget and economics in the U.S. Treasury and Senate Budget Committee.

President Obama also announced his intent to appoint Thomas R. Nides as Chairman of the Board of Trustees of the Woodrow Wilson International Center for Scholars. Nides is currently Vice Chairman of Morgan Stanley and previously served as Deputy Secretary for Management and Resources at the Department of State.

Laura Paulson will be appointed as a Member of the Committee for the Preservation of the White House. She is currently Chairman of Americas at Christie's and a Senior International Director in Post-War and Contemporary Art.

Quyen D. Chu and Anhlan P. Nguyen will both be appointed as Members of the Board of Directors of the Vietnam Education Foundation. Chu is Chief of Surgical Oncology at LSU Health Science Center and Nguyen is an IT Portfolio Manager at the University of Texas MD Anderson Cancer Center.